-- Rosneft Obtains $16.8 Billion in Loans to Finance TNK-BP Deal
-- B y   W i l l   K e n n e d y
-- 2012-12-24T12:16:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/rosneft-obtains-16-8-billion-in-loans-to-finance-tnk-bp-deal.html
OAO Rosneft,  Russia ’s largest oil
producer, signed loan agreements for $16.8 billion to finance
the acquisition of TNK-BP.  Rosneft will borrow $4.1 billion for five years and $12.7
billion for two years from a group of international banks. The
cash will pay for  BP Plc (BP/) ’s 50 percent stake in Russia’s third-
largest oil producer, the Moscow-based company said in a
statement today.  The state-run oil producer, led by former deputy prime
minister and close Vladimir Putin associate  Igor Sechin , has
signed seperate agreements with BP and a group of billionaires
to buy all of TNK-BP. The deals will make Rosneft the world’s
largest publicly traded producer of crude oil.  The lending banks include Bank of America Corp., Barclays
Plc, BNP Paribas SA, Citigroup Inc., Credit Agricole SA, ING
Groep NV, Intesa Sanpaolo SpA, JPMorgan Chase & Co., Mizuho
Financial Group Inc., Nordea Bank AB, SMBC, Societe Generale SA
UniCredit SpA.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at 
 wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  